  "prompt": "What was the public's reaction to Crystal Pepsi?",
  "response": "When Crystal Pepsi was launched in 1992, it generated a lot of buzz and curiosity due to its unique clear cola appearance. Many consumers were initially intrigued by the novelty of a clear cola and were eager to try it. However, the public's reaction was mixed. While some people enjoyed the taste and appreciated the innovation, many others were disappointed because it did not taste like regular Pepsi. \n\nThe novelty of the clear cola wore off quickly, and sales dropped significantly after the initial launch. Some consumers felt that the taste was too similar to existing lemon-lime sodas, and it did not meet their expectations for a cola. As a result, Crystal Pepsi was discontinued in 1993, less than a year after its introduction.\n\nIn recent years, there has been a nostalgic revival of interest in Crystal Pepsi. It has been re-released multiple times as a limited edition product, and each time it has garnered significant attention and sales. This suggests that while the initial public reaction was not overwhelmingly positive, there is now a segment of consumers who fondly remember Crystal Pepsi and are eager to relive the experience.",
